1
00:00:08,600 --> 00:00:10,961
♪Love's little quiz
takes seven parts sweet♪

2
00:00:10,962 --> 00:00:13,559
♪And three parts bitter,
till you and I meet♪

3
00:00:13,560 --> 00:00:17,159
♪I pretend I'm not there,
but secretly stay♪

4
00:00:17,160 --> 00:00:26,399
♪Waiting for you♪

5
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:31,400
♪We've got so many
romantic dreams to unfold♪

6
00:00:31,480 --> 00:00:36,224
♪Finally hearing
the I love you I long to hold♪

7
00:00:36,225 --> 00:00:39,839
♪Falling fast
into the swirl of your eyes♪

8
00:00:39,840 --> 00:00:42,399
♪It's just too tempting, so tempting♪

9
00:00:42,400 --> 00:00:45,499
♪Never could I have guessed♪

10
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:46,499
♪My heart's rhythm♪

11
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:49,632
♪How beautiful it is, meeting you♪

12
00:01:02,975 --> 00:01:05,961
=Late to Love=
(Adapted from "My Husband Is A Billionaire!")

13
00:01:05,962 --> 00:01:08,920
=Episode 15=

14
00:01:10,859 --> 00:01:11,900
Grandma,

15
00:01:12,339 --> 00:01:15,179
the truth is almost out.

16
00:01:15,699 --> 00:01:17,539
You got worse

17
00:01:17,820 --> 00:01:19,739
because someone gave you

18
00:01:20,300 --> 00:01:22,340
an experimental drug.

19
00:01:24,380 --> 00:01:26,260
Code name, NIT-33.

20
00:01:26,540 --> 00:01:28,179
It's from United Pharma.

21
00:01:28,540 --> 00:01:30,900
It's tiny, almost undetectable.

22
00:01:31,139 --> 00:01:32,618
But it builds up over time

23
00:01:32,619 --> 00:01:33,860
and speeds up aging.

24
00:01:35,219 --> 00:01:37,780
Ye Xin thought she left no trace.

25
00:01:38,259 --> 00:01:39,980
I won't let her get away.

26
00:01:40,380 --> 00:01:41,500
Grandma,

27
00:01:41,619 --> 00:01:42,379
I only bought

28
00:01:42,380 --> 00:01:43,819
into United Pharma

29
00:01:43,820 --> 00:01:45,459
to get their books,

30
00:01:45,460 --> 00:01:46,379
lab records,

31
00:01:46,380 --> 00:01:48,058
buried emails,

32
00:01:48,059 --> 00:01:49,459
and approval files.

33
00:01:49,460 --> 00:01:50,700
Don't worry.

34
00:01:51,259 --> 00:01:53,019
Ye Xin won't be charged

35
00:01:54,059 --> 00:01:55,980
with malpractice.

36
00:01:56,100 --> 00:01:57,780
It'll be attempted murder.

37
00:02:00,419 --> 00:02:02,140
And Dr. X.

38
00:02:03,859 --> 00:02:06,179
He was one of the first to study NIT.

39
00:02:06,180 --> 00:02:08,099
He wasn't just watching.

40
00:02:08,740 --> 00:02:10,180
He was part of it.

41
00:02:19,580 --> 00:02:23,019
He's faster than I thought.

42
00:02:23,020 --> 00:02:24,979
NIT...

43
00:02:25,020 --> 00:02:27,220
He even found the code name.

44
00:02:27,379 --> 00:02:28,580
Huo Group

45
00:02:28,659 --> 00:02:29,498
is now United Pharma's

46
00:02:29,499 --> 00:02:31,019
second-largest shareholder.

47
00:02:31,020 --> 00:02:33,460
It became official last week.

48
00:02:33,860 --> 00:02:37,060
You let the wolf right in.

49
00:02:38,339 --> 00:02:41,379
At least we're hidden.

50
00:02:41,980 --> 00:02:43,220
Well,

51
00:02:43,460 --> 00:02:45,580
this should prove where I stand.

52
00:02:47,020 --> 00:02:49,939
Here's to our partnership.

53
00:02:52,819 --> 00:02:54,218
One thing still bothers me.

54
00:02:54,219 --> 00:02:55,979
Dr. X.

55
00:02:56,180 --> 00:02:57,618
Why is he after you?

56
00:02:57,619 --> 00:02:59,060
Did you fall out?

57
00:02:59,219 --> 00:03:01,459
I don't even know him.

58
00:03:01,460 --> 00:03:03,218
What I don't get

59
00:03:03,219 --> 00:03:04,739
is how a total stranger

60
00:03:04,740 --> 00:03:05,778
knows so much

61
00:03:05,779 --> 00:03:07,859
about NIT's old research.

62
00:03:07,860 --> 00:03:08,938
I already checked

63
00:03:08,939 --> 00:03:11,300
every contractor on the line.

64
00:03:12,140 --> 00:03:13,500
What about temps?

65
00:03:14,339 --> 00:03:15,780
Interns?

66
00:03:17,020 --> 00:03:20,060
Huo Zichen, don't be ridiculous.

67
00:03:20,140 --> 00:03:21,378
This is a cutting-edge

68
00:03:21,379 --> 00:03:23,979
drug research.

69
00:03:24,020 --> 00:03:24,979
What intern

70
00:03:24,980 --> 00:03:26,579
would know that much

71
00:03:26,580 --> 00:03:28,659
and be that academically sharp?

72
00:03:31,779 --> 00:03:33,340
You have a lead?

73
00:03:33,860 --> 00:03:35,139
I need to confirm it.

74
00:03:38,379 --> 00:03:39,300
Shen Yan,

75
00:03:39,499 --> 00:03:40,859
move tomorrow's board meeting

76
00:03:40,860 --> 00:03:42,300
for 8 a.m.

77
00:03:42,740 --> 00:03:44,020
I have an announcement.

78
00:04:04,750 --> 00:04:10,182
♪Darling, you go far away♪

79
00:04:11,175 --> 00:04:16,532
♪Why don't you take me too?♪

80
00:04:18,162 --> 00:04:24,070
♪We could go on a journey♪

81
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:30,957
♪I could take you in♪

82
00:04:31,937 --> 00:04:37,870
♪Garfunkel's got Simon♪

83
00:04:38,512 --> 00:04:44,745
♪Batman's got Robin too♪

84
00:04:45,687 --> 00:04:52,574
♪Everyone's got a partner♪

85
00:04:52,575 --> 00:04:58,724
♪Trained to help them through♪

86
00:04:58,725 --> 00:05:05,082
♪Cause it's hard to travel alone♪

87
00:05:05,725 --> 00:05:09,411
♪So you might as well just take me♪

88
00:05:09,412 --> 00:05:11,949
♪You might as well have company♪

89
00:05:11,950 --> 00:05:19,395
♪And if you should fall in love♪

90
00:05:19,875 --> 00:05:22,849
♪It wouldn't be the worst thing♪

91
00:05:22,850 --> 00:05:27,178
♪Cause you wouldn't be the only one♪

92
00:05:27,179 --> 00:05:28,900
(Nange,)

93
00:05:29,779 --> 00:05:31,820
(once I find Dr. X,)

94
00:05:32,299 --> 00:05:34,340
(I'll give you a wedding.)

95
00:05:54,020 --> 00:05:55,338
Zichen.

96
00:05:55,339 --> 00:05:57,259
Ever since that family dinner,

97
00:05:57,260 --> 00:05:58,979
we've felt that...

98
00:06:00,260 --> 00:06:01,858
We're family now.

99
00:06:01,859 --> 00:06:03,139
We should be closer.

100
00:06:03,140 --> 00:06:05,139
But whenever we call Beiyan,

101
00:06:05,140 --> 00:06:07,778
he's either busy
or his assistant picks up.

102
00:06:07,779 --> 00:06:09,658
They're polite enough,

103
00:06:09,659 --> 00:06:11,658
but they never let anything slip.

104
00:06:11,659 --> 00:06:13,538
We get nowhere.

105
00:06:13,539 --> 00:06:16,460
Is that how in-laws act?

106
00:06:16,500 --> 00:06:17,499
Shen Yan

107
00:06:17,500 --> 00:06:18,858
works closely with my cousin.

108
00:06:18,859 --> 00:06:20,899
He's just careful.

109
00:06:20,900 --> 00:06:22,459
Please don't take it to heart.

110
00:06:22,460 --> 00:06:24,419
How can we not?

111
00:06:24,539 --> 00:06:26,538
We're trying to be close.

112
00:06:26,539 --> 00:06:28,699
Now we look pushy.

113
00:06:28,700 --> 00:06:30,538
Yin says the same.

114
00:06:30,539 --> 00:06:32,538
She wants to learn

115
00:06:32,539 --> 00:06:34,619
from the Huo family, but...

116
00:06:38,219 --> 00:06:38,939
Actually,

117
00:06:38,940 --> 00:06:40,978
that's why I came.

118
00:06:40,979 --> 00:06:42,979
I know a few

119
00:06:43,299 --> 00:06:45,739
private clubs and art salons.

120
00:06:45,820 --> 00:06:47,259
They're good for networking.

121
00:06:47,260 --> 00:06:48,699
If you're interested,

122
00:06:48,700 --> 00:06:50,940
I can take you there.

123
00:06:51,500 --> 00:06:52,579
Sure.

124
00:06:52,580 --> 00:06:54,259
That sounds great.

125
00:06:54,260 --> 00:06:55,298
Young people

126
00:06:55,299 --> 00:06:57,098
should go out more.

127
00:06:57,099 --> 00:06:59,819
Why stay with us old folks?

128
00:06:59,820 --> 00:07:00,738
Alright.

129
00:07:00,739 --> 00:07:02,418
Zichen, don't just sit there.

130
00:07:02,419 --> 00:07:03,059
Didn't a new

131
00:07:03,060 --> 00:07:04,658
dessert shop open downstairs?

132
00:07:04,659 --> 00:07:06,700
Take Zichen there.

133
00:07:08,060 --> 00:07:09,220
- Okay.
- Go on.

134
00:07:10,099 --> 00:07:12,139
Then I'll excuse myself.

135
00:07:12,140 --> 00:07:13,380
Go on. Have fun.

136
00:07:14,460 --> 00:07:15,539
I'm going.

137
00:07:17,339 --> 00:07:18,780
Don't rush back.

138
00:07:22,020 --> 00:07:24,299
If Yinyin can win over Zichen...

139
00:07:26,339 --> 00:07:27,340
Not bad.

140
00:07:27,779 --> 00:07:30,340
Zichen, try some.

141
00:07:30,500 --> 00:07:32,220
This place is famous.

142
00:07:32,940 --> 00:07:34,099
Forget dessert.

143
00:07:34,179 --> 00:07:35,780
I'm interested in you.

144
00:07:36,539 --> 00:07:37,939
Xu Nange is impressive.

145
00:07:37,940 --> 00:07:39,700
You must be too.

146
00:07:40,979 --> 00:07:43,059
How can I compare to her?

147
00:07:43,779 --> 00:07:44,899
Don't say that.

148
00:07:44,900 --> 00:07:46,139
I was abroad for years.

149
00:07:46,140 --> 00:07:47,419
I'm curious

150
00:07:47,739 --> 00:07:49,379
what you and Nange

151
00:07:49,380 --> 00:07:50,739
went through.

152
00:07:50,859 --> 00:07:52,179
You two

153
00:07:52,219 --> 00:07:53,538
must have had

154
00:07:53,539 --> 00:07:55,460
interesting internships.

155
00:07:57,620 --> 00:07:58,619
Well,

156
00:07:58,620 --> 00:08:00,259
I studied fashion design

157
00:08:00,260 --> 00:08:02,260
with a Milan designer.

158
00:08:02,580 --> 00:08:04,098
My mentor was...

159
00:08:04,099 --> 00:08:04,738
What about Nange?

160
00:08:04,739 --> 00:08:06,140
Who cares about her?

161
00:08:08,739 --> 00:08:09,659
I...

162
00:08:09,940 --> 00:08:11,819
I didn't really notice.

163
00:08:11,820 --> 00:08:12,579
She...

164
00:08:12,580 --> 00:08:14,499
was always so secretive.

165
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:15,619
I think

166
00:08:15,620 --> 00:08:17,658
she interned at a big pharma company.

167
00:08:17,659 --> 00:08:19,098
Uh...

168
00:08:19,099 --> 00:08:21,419
The famous one...

169
00:08:21,539 --> 00:08:22,820
United Pharma.

170
00:08:23,419 --> 00:08:25,418
That's all I know.

171
00:08:25,419 --> 00:08:27,940
(United Pharma internship?)

172
00:08:28,539 --> 00:08:30,340
(Xu Nange,)

173
00:08:30,620 --> 00:08:31,619
(one secret)

174
00:08:31,620 --> 00:08:33,739
(leads to another.)

175
00:08:33,779 --> 00:08:35,460
(Interesting.)

176
00:08:35,900 --> 00:08:36,578
Zichen,

177
00:08:36,579 --> 00:08:37,379
let me tell you

178
00:08:37,380 --> 00:08:38,940
about my internship.

179
00:08:39,059 --> 00:08:40,099
My mentor

180
00:08:40,100 --> 00:08:41,499
came to China for the first time.

181
00:08:41,500 --> 00:08:43,259
Her company was hard to get into.

182
00:08:43,260 --> 00:08:44,578
When I first met her...

183
00:08:44,579 --> 00:08:44,979
Okay.

184
00:08:44,980 --> 00:08:45,979
My mentor...

185
00:08:46,380 --> 00:08:48,499
I just remembered something urgent.

186
00:08:48,699 --> 00:08:49,739
I'll take you

187
00:08:49,740 --> 00:08:51,298
to the art salon next time.

188
00:08:51,299 --> 00:08:52,820
I should go.

189
00:08:54,779 --> 00:08:56,458
Zichen, the dessert...

190
00:08:56,459 --> 00:08:57,820
Zichen!

191
00:09:42,059 --> 00:09:43,060
Morning.

192
00:09:43,299 --> 00:09:44,418
(What happened?)

193
00:09:44,419 --> 00:09:46,379
(He was in a meeting.)

194
00:09:46,380 --> 00:09:47,818
(I was waiting.)

195
00:09:47,819 --> 00:09:50,058
(Then... what happened?)

196
00:09:50,059 --> 00:09:51,499
Breakfast is ready.

197
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:52,658
Chinese or Western.

198
00:09:52,659 --> 00:09:53,739
Your choice.

199
00:09:59,819 --> 00:10:01,538
(No way.)

200
00:10:01,539 --> 00:10:03,938
(I was so looking forward
to our first night.)

201
00:10:03,939 --> 00:10:05,658
(Such a perfect night,)

202
00:10:05,659 --> 00:10:07,700
(and I slept right through it?)

203
00:10:11,939 --> 00:10:15,060
Xu Nange, what's on your mind?

204
00:10:17,860 --> 00:10:20,019
Nothing.

205
00:10:21,340 --> 00:10:23,099
You slept well last night.

206
00:10:23,100 --> 00:10:24,379
I know.

207
00:10:28,260 --> 00:10:29,379
Xu Nange,

208
00:10:29,900 --> 00:10:31,859
were you expecting something?

209
00:10:32,419 --> 00:10:33,940
No.

210
00:10:34,059 --> 00:10:35,139
No?

211
00:10:35,500 --> 00:10:36,698
- No.
- Really?

212
00:10:36,699 --> 00:10:37,940
Really.

213
00:10:42,220 --> 00:10:43,379
I need to take this.

214
00:10:44,380 --> 00:10:45,099
Hello?

215
00:10:45,100 --> 00:10:46,180
Nange,

216
00:10:46,779 --> 00:10:49,139
did someone break into your lab?

217
00:10:49,500 --> 00:10:50,660
What?

218
00:10:50,779 --> 00:10:52,019
The lock was picked.

219
00:10:52,020 --> 00:10:53,940
The footage is gone.

220
00:10:57,779 --> 00:10:59,940
Nange, you're finally here.

221
00:11:00,779 --> 00:11:02,379
What a mess.

222
00:11:02,380 --> 00:11:04,060
Did you call the police?

223
00:11:04,699 --> 00:11:07,178
Yes. They just left.

224
00:11:07,179 --> 00:11:09,499
They found nothing.

225
00:11:09,500 --> 00:11:10,538
Okay.

226
00:11:10,539 --> 00:11:12,219
I'll check it myself.

227
00:11:12,220 --> 00:11:14,538
Okay, then I'll go to security.

228
00:11:14,539 --> 00:11:15,420
Okay.

229
00:11:23,179 --> 00:11:25,259
They left no trace.

230
00:11:25,260 --> 00:11:26,220
Nange,

231
00:11:26,740 --> 00:11:29,019
why care so much about this paper?

232
00:11:29,220 --> 00:11:30,339
I've read it.

233
00:11:30,340 --> 00:11:32,739
It's a normal topic.

234
00:11:33,100 --> 00:11:35,139
It is.

235
00:11:35,140 --> 00:11:36,578
But I...

236
00:11:36,579 --> 00:11:38,700
You can delay graduation

237
00:11:38,860 --> 00:11:40,219
or change topics

238
00:11:40,220 --> 00:11:41,660
if it isn't working.

239
00:11:43,020 --> 00:11:43,899
I've put

240
00:11:43,900 --> 00:11:45,739
too much into this.

241
00:11:45,740 --> 00:11:47,779
I can't just change it.

242
00:11:49,299 --> 00:11:50,460
I can help.

243
00:11:50,659 --> 00:11:51,418
You've got me

244
00:11:51,419 --> 00:11:52,580
and the Huo family.

245
00:11:54,340 --> 00:11:55,259
Beiyan,

246
00:11:55,260 --> 00:11:55,938
to me,

247
00:11:55,939 --> 00:11:57,658
this isn't just a dissertation.

248
00:11:57,659 --> 00:11:58,460
I...

249
00:11:59,539 --> 00:12:00,460
It...

250
00:12:01,500 --> 00:12:02,460
No.

251
00:12:04,140 --> 00:12:05,580
I think

252
00:12:06,140 --> 00:12:08,379
you care too much about this.

253
00:12:08,779 --> 00:12:11,219
Is there another reason?

254
00:12:11,220 --> 00:12:12,580
I can help.

255
00:12:12,939 --> 00:12:14,099
No.

256
00:12:14,220 --> 00:12:16,099
I'm just stressed.

257
00:12:16,659 --> 00:12:18,340
I'll go find Professor Liang.

258
00:12:50,087 --> 00:12:53,861
♪What destiny brought us to meet♪

259
00:12:53,862 --> 00:12:57,182
♪Two different worlds, a love so sweet♪

260
00:12:57,187 --> 00:13:00,561
♪A wish we made
in a past life, it seems♪

261
00:13:00,562 --> 00:13:03,416
♪Destined to cross time and dream ♪

262
00:13:03,417 --> 00:13:07,257
♪Like a fairytale story told♪

263
00:13:07,337 --> 00:13:10,594
♪A gentle breeze feels so bold♪

264
00:13:10,612 --> 00:13:14,298
♪As your hair brushes past your ear♪

265
00:13:14,299 --> 00:13:16,656
♪I long to kiss your cheek, my dear♪

266
00:13:16,657 --> 00:13:20,896
♪All my longing, all my love for you♪

267
00:13:20,897 --> 00:13:23,457
♪Has never changed, it's forever true♪

268
00:13:23,899 --> 00:13:30,297
♪It's the hand of fate
that we meet again♪

269
00:13:31,099 --> 00:13:35,537
♪Let me hold you once again♪

270
00:13:35,787 --> 00:13:38,707
♪Resting against your chest♪

271
00:13:39,057 --> 00:13:44,298
♪Your warmth shines like stars at night♪

272
00:13:44,299 --> 00:13:49,098
♪Let me kiss you once again♪

273
00:13:49,099 --> 00:13:51,898
♪No reason needed♪

274
00:13:51,899 --> 00:13:54,096
♪My heart belongs to you♪

275
00:13:54,097 --> 00:13:59,817
♪I'm not afraid
to cross time to find you♪

